text: Laurence R. Young is an American physicist currently the Apollo Program Professor Emeritus of Astronautics at Massachusetts Institute of Technology and an Elected Fellow of the Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers, the Biomedical Engineering Society and the American Institute for Medical and Biological Engineering. ==References== Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Living people Category:Massachusetts Institute of Technology faculty Category:21st-century American physicists Category:Fellow Members of the IEEE Category:Massachusetts Institute of Technology alumni Category:Fellows of the American Institute for Medical and Biological Engineering Category:Fellows of the Biomedical Engineering Society
